            . I am a <rs id="t18220220-8-viclabel45" type="occupation">confectioner</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220220-8-victim136 t18220220-8-viclabel45"></join>, and live in <placeName id="t18220220-8-crimeloc46">Catharine-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18220220-8-crimeloc46" type="placeName" value="Catharine-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18220220-8-crimeloc46" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18220220-8-off43 t18220220-8-crimeloc46"></join>. On Saturday night, about seven o'clock, I lost my shew-glass out of the shop, with about 5 lbs. of sugared almonds in it; it was safe a quarter of an hour before - I did not miss it till the prisoner was brought back with it.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18220220-8-person138">
                  JAMES 
                  PRETTY
               <interp inst="t18220220-8-person138" type="surname" value="PRETTY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-8-person138" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18220220-8-person138" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am porter to Mr. Wilkins. On Saturday night, about seven o'clock, I was coming up Catharine-street, and saw the prisoner and a boy a little taller than him, going along together with the shew glass; I pursued him, the prisoner had the glass - I brought him back to the shop; his companion ran off - he began crying, and said he could get no work.</p>
               <p>THOMAS WILLIS. I am a constable. I was sent for, and took him in charge.</p>
               <p>(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I picked the glass up by his door, I did not know it was his.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18220220-8-verdict47" type="verdictDescription">
